Mobile Navigation QA Guide (Jolly Commerce)

Theme: Jolly Commerce - Mobile Navigation Rework
Customizer: [link]
Section: Header
Blocks: (See details below)

Design: [link]

Testing Overview:

This guide covers testing the reworked mobile navigation. Desktop navigation is not affected. Mobile and desktop navigations are now independent.

Visual Testing:

Thoroughly test the appearance and behavior of the entire mobile menu and its components. Exclude the section highlighted in green in the design document. The cards displayed when dropdowns are open (as shown in the screenshot) do not require testing.

Functional Testing:

*   **Settings Testing:** Verify that all settings for the new blocks function as expected by the user.
*   **Bestseller Swiper:**
    *   Ensure swiping functions correctly.
    *   Verify that clicking an image redirects to the assigned link (configure links in the Customizer). The first block should already have a link assigned.
*   **CTA:**
    *   If no text is entered, the CTA should be hidden.
    *   If a link is present, clicking the CTA should redirect to the specified URL. If no link is present, clicking should have no effect.
*   **Dropdowns:**
    *   Confirm that dropdowns open and close correctly.
    *   Verify that clicking a card within a dropdown redirects to the correct page.
*   **Review Block:**
    *   If a metaobject is specified, data should be retrieved from it.
    *   If a value is specified in a setting *and* a metaobject is specified, the setting value should override the metaobject value (refer to the settings description for details).
*   **Link Block:**
    *   If no title is entered, the link block should be hidden.
    *   If a URL is specified, clicking the block should redirect to the URL. If no URL is specified, clicking should have no effect.

Resources:

*   Design: [link]
*   Customizer: [link] (Useful Info section)

Details:

This rework focuses solely on the mobile navigation within the Header section.

Key Features:

*   Mobile Menu: This section is already present in the Jolly Commerce theme.
*   Best Sellers: Displayed as an image with a link and a title. Links are added manually in the Customizer.
*   Default Tabs: Option to have tabs (Collections, Accessories, Lifestyle) open by default.

QA Guide:
Theme: Jolly Commerce - Mobile Navigation rework
Customizer: link
Section: Header
Blocks: 

Design: link
Visual testing
Do full testing of the menu and all of its components that we see on mobile. Do not test the section highlighted in green:

No need to test cards on screenshot below (seen when dropdowns are open):
 

Functional testing

Important: do settings testing (as usual - whether they work as user is expecting them to work) for new 3 blocks (details below)

Bestseller Swiper: 
Swiping and redirect to another when the image is clicked. In order for redirect to work, you have to assign a link to a block in the customizer (first one is set up already)


CTA: no text - hidden, link present - redirect to the specified url, no link - no redirect


Dropdowns: opening closing works, clicking on a card redirects you to another page


Review block: metaobject present - data is retrieved from it; specifying a value in a setting, while metaobject is specified too, overrides the value from the same metaobject (see settings description on how it works)



Link block: no title - hidden, url specified - redirect to it, no url - no redirect






Design : 
Customizer link : 
1. Useful Info


2. summary of what has to be done
What has to be done :
Mobile navigation

Mobile and desktop will not be linked anymore ‚Üí These will be two different navigations


3. All about tasks  
What we want : 

Mobile menu 

Is this section already in the theme ?  YES
Is this section a jolly section ?  YES

Functional aspect :
Best sellers ‚Üí It will be an image, a link and a title ‚Üí link will be added manually
We will have the possibility to open by default the tabs (Collections, accessories, lifestyle)
After this, no specific functional aspect


4. What is already developed  
What we do not want : 
Change desktop navigation ‚Üí Only a mobile change
